text: Kyzyl-Yulduz () is a rural locality (a village) in Bazitamaksky Selsoviet, Ilishevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 85 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 35 km from Verkhneyarkeyevo, 2 km from Bazitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ilishevsky District
title: Kyzyl-Yulduz, Ilishevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
